    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="1086"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1086">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3886.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Canada</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department anxiously awaits the name of the one American delivered to judicial
                    authorities at Aguascalientes mentioned in your April 27. Do everything possible
                    to see that he has a fair trial and that no summary action is taken until
                    Department’s agents can make proper representations in his behalf.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
